{"cursor":"8963","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Convention\n| name = Hal-Con Sci-Fi, Fantasy & Comic Convention image = caption = status =\n| Active genre = Multigenre venue = World Trade and Convention Centre location =\n| Halifax, Nova Scotia country = Canada first = last = organizer = HAL-CON Sci-\n| Fi Fantasy Association filing = Not-For-Profit attendance = Est. 6000 website\n| = http://www.hal-con.com\n}}\n\n'Hal-Con Sci-Fi, Fantasy & Comic Convention', commonly known as 'Hal-Con', was\nfounded in the 1970s and revived in the 2010s. It is traditionally an annual\nweekend event held in Halifax, Nova Scotia in Atlantic Canada and held at the\nend of fall.\n\nOriginally showcasing comic books, games, science fiction/fantasy and\nfilm/television, and related popular arts, it has grown to encompass the full\nspectrum of geekdom, including Comic Books, Science Fiction, Fantasy, Gaming,\nCyberpunk, Steampunk, Renaissance, Anime, Furry, Cyber goth, Cosplay, and\nanything else of the fantastical while still having enough appeal for even the\nmost casual fan. The gathering includes entertainment for most tastes from\nmusic, stage show, and small social gaming circles, and the chance to rub elbows\nwith the famous and infamous of geek pop-culture.\n\nHal-Con 2013 is returning November 8th-10th, 2012 at World Trade and\nConvention Centre.\n","linknr":208,"url":"Hal-Con","recorded":1375089013,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Hal-Con&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Hal-Con&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vecto